# Hierarchical trees (`@he-tree/vue`)

## When this applies

Use this rule whenever the renderer shows a **hierarchical tree** (expand/collapse, nested folders, drag-reorder, checkboxes on branches, or similar). Examples: project worlds, document browsers, template hierarchies, settings trees with nested groups.

## Required library (full replacement)

- **Use [`@he-tree/vue`](https://hetree.phphe.com/)** exclusively (`BaseTree`, `Draggable`, helpers such as `walkTreeData`).
- **Never** use Quasar **`QTree`** / **`q-tree`** anywhere in this repository — not for small trees, not for prototypes, not in Storybook product previews. **`@he-tree/vue`** is the **only** approved tree implementation for Fantasia Archive.
- Do not add **`QTree`** to new code and remove any legacy **`QTree`** usage when you touch that surface.

## Imports and styles

```ts
import { BaseTree, Draggable } from '@he-tree/vue'
import '@he-tree/vue/style/default.css'
```

- Import the default stylesheet **once** per tree surface (feature SFC or a dedicated wrapper SFC). Override visuals in feature **`styles/`** SCSS with BEM + semantic tokens — do not fork the library CSS wholesale.
- Prefer **`Draggable`** when users may reorder nodes; **`BaseTree`** for read-only or selection-only trees.
- **List DnD policy:** tree reorder uses **he-tree** built-in drag-and-drop only — **do not** wrap nodes with **`vue-draggable-plus`** ([fa-drag-drop-lists.mdc](fa-drag-drop-lists.mdc)).

## Virtualization (performance)

- Enable **`virtualization`** when the tree may hold **roughly 50+ visible rows** or deep expand-all paths.
- The tree or a **bounded parent** must have an explicit **`height`** or **`max-height`** (fixed pixel height or flex child with a constrained scroll area). Virtualization does not work on an unbounded auto-height container.
- Combine virtualization with **lazy child loading** from SQLite when branches are loaded on expand (see **`.cursor/skills/fantasia-sqlite-main/SKILL.md`**).

## Project layout

- **Thin Vue SFC** — template slots, `data-test-locator`, i18n **`$t`**, Quasar icons/buttons inside **`#default`** node slots.
- **Feature `scripts/`** — tree data mapping, expand state, filter/search, DnD handlers wired to Pinia or IPC.
- **`src/scripts/faHeTree/`** — shared pure helpers (flatten, walk, id maps) when two or more features need the same tree utilities.
- **Types** — shared node shapes under repo-root **`types/`** (`app/types/...`); do not add colocated `*.types.ts` under **`src/`**.

## Styling and Quasar

- Node rows may use Quasar **`q-icon`**, **`q-checkbox`**, **`q-btn`**, and **`fa-text-*`** / **`fa-icon-*`** classes inside the **`#default`** slot.
- Wrap the scroll region with **`hasScrollbar`** when vertical scrollbar presence may shift layout ([`scrollbar.scss`](../../src/css/globals/scrollbar.scss)).
- Add **`data-test-locator`** on the tree root and on interactive node chrome per [vue-template-test-hooks.mdc](vue-template-test-hooks.mdc).

